@startuml AI_Red_Teaming_States

' ============================================
' STATE DIAGRAM: AI Red Teaming Engagement Lifecycle
' Bug Bounty and Its Simulation Platform
' ============================================

title AI Red Teaming Engagement State Transitions

[*] --> Draft : Organization creates AI testing request

Draft --> Published : Publish engagement
Draft --> [*] : Cancel draft

Published --> Inviting : Send expert invitations
Inviting --> Assigned : AI security expert accepted
Inviting --> Cancelled : No responses (timeout 7 days)

Assigned --> In_Progress : Expert starts testing
In_Progress --> Testing : Active attack execution
Testing --> Vulnerability_Found : AI vulnerability discovered
Testing --> No_Issues : Testing complete, no issues

Vulnerability_Found --> Documenting : Document findings
Documenting --> Report_Draft : Compile vulnerability report
Report_Draft --> Report_Submitted : Submit findings

Report_Submitted --> Under_Review : Org reviews findings
Under_Review --> Clarification_Needed : Org requests details
Under_Review --> Validated : Org confirms vulnerability

Clarification_Needed --> Report_Submitted : Expert provides clarification

Validated --> Fixing : Org applies fixes
Fixing --> Retest_Requested : Request retest
Retest_Requested --> Retesting : Expert retests fixes

Retesting --> Retest_Passed : Vulnerability fixed
Retesting --> Retest_Failed : Still vulnerable

Retest_Failed --> Fixing : Continue fixing
Retest_Passed --> Approved : Approve engagement completion

No_Issues --> Report_Submitted : Submit clean report
Approved --> Payment_Pending : Approve payment
Payment_Pending --> Paid : Payment processed
Paid --> Closed : Archive engagement

Cancelled --> [*]
Closed --> [*]

note right of Testing
  Attack types:
  - Prompt injection
  - Jailbreaking
  - Data poisoning
  - Model inversion
  - Adversarial examples
  - Bias exploitation
end note

note right of Vulnerability_Found
  AI vulnerability categories:
  - Unauthorized access
  - Data leakage
  - Model manipulation
  - Bias exploitation
  - Safety bypass
end note

note right of Retesting
  Retest cycle:
  - Max 3 retest rounds
  - Each round: 5-10 days
  - Payment adjusted if multiple rounds
end note

@enduml
